            <title>[LUCENE-2043] Fix CommitIndexTask to also commit IndexReader changes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2043</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m setting up a benchmark for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1458&quot; title=&quot;Further steps towards flexible indexing&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1458&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and one limitation I hit is that the CommitIndexTask doesn&apos;t commit pending changes in the IndexReader (eg via DeleteByPercent), using a named commit point.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
